# AOR Common Taxonomy

## Purpose

Keep package responsibilities explicit inside `packages/aor-common/*`.

## Rules

1. `@aor/types` contains only:
   - Zod schemas.
   - TypeScript types directly inferred from Zod schemas (`z.infer`).
   - DTO contracts derived from those schemas.

2. `@aor/types` must not contain:
   - Business rules/functions.
   - String/date formatting helpers.
   - Persistence label encoders/decoders.
   - DI tokens.

3. Shared pure business logic must live in `@aor/domain`.

4. Shared technical implementations that implement adapter contracts (crypto adapters, provider wrappers)
   must live in `@aor/adapters`.

5. Shared pure utilities (date/string formatting, parsing helpers, deterministic mappers)
   must live in `@aor/utils`.

6. Shared logging contracts/implementations must live in `@aor/logger`.

7. `@aor/adapters` must not host generic helpers or logger primitives.

8. Shared application ports/contracts and related DI symbols must live in `@aor/ports`.

9. Use-case DI symbols (application orchestration tokens) must stay local to backend presentation modules
   (e.g. `applications/backend/src/presentation/**/**.tokens.ts`) and must not be moved to `@aor/ports`.
